<br>
&gt;Judge people not by the rumors or actions of a few members of their guild. <br>
<br>
Rumble, that is exactly what a guild is.  It is a group of people you associate with, who uphold (or bring down) your reputation as you affect theirs in return.  I am not about to shun or berate members of the Order as I meet them only because of this issue, but I'd be lying if I said I wouldn't remember it.  I don't think I am being unfair at all, I think I'm just being open about human nature.  Almost everyone acts on the same impulse, and it's entirely fair.<br>
<br>
If you believe some members of your guild are not acting honorably and are damaging the reputation of your guild, get your officers and guild leader on the matter, accept the collateral damage to your own reputation, or find a new guild.  Those are your options.  I'm not trying to attack you, I'm just trying to help.  This is the reality of having a guild.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
